From: retropangui-c5 build <build@retropangui-c5>
Date: Fri, 15 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] gpu: mali: fix hwcnt mcu_on state leak on firmware init failure

kbase_csf_firmware_load_init() calls boot_csf_firmware() which invokes
kbase_hwcnt_backend_csf_on_after_mcu_on() unconditionally, setting the
hwcnt backend's internal mcu_on flag to true.

If a subsequent step (e.g. global_init_on_boot) fails and the function
returns via err_out, kbase_csf_firmware_unload_term() is called.
unload_term() calls kbase_pm_wait_for_desired_state() with mcu_desired=false,
but because firmware_inited is still false at that point, the PM state
machine stays at KBASE_MCU_OFF and never transitions through
KBASE_MCU_ON_PEND_HALT -- so kbase_hwcnt_backend_csf_on_after_mcu_off()
is never called.

On a subsequent retry or probe, kbase_hwcnt_backend_csf_on_before_mcu_cold_boot()
fires a WARN_ON(csf_info->mcu_on) because mcu_on is still true from the
previous failed attempt.

Fix: track whether boot_csf_firmware() was reached. If so, call
kbase_hwcnt_backend_csf_on_after_mcu_off() in the error path before
delegating to unload_term().
---
 common_drivers/drivers/gpu/arm/midgard/csf/mali_kbase_csf_firmware.c | 9 +++++++--
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/common_drivers/drivers/gpu/arm/midgard/csf/mali_kbase_csf_firmware.c
+++ b/common_drivers/drivers/gpu/arm/midgard/csf/mali_kbase_csf_firmware.c
@@ -2539,6 +2539,7 @@ int kbase_csf_firmware_load_init(struct kbase_device *kbdev)
 	u32 entry_end_offset;
 	u32 entry_offset;
 	int ret;
+	bool mcu_boot_attempted = false;
 	const char *fw_name = default_fw_name;

 	lockdep_assert_held(&kbdev->fw_load_lock);
@@ -2705,7 +2706,9 @@ int kbase_csf_firmware_load_init(struct kbase_device *kbdev)
 	if (ret != 0)
 		goto err_out;

+	/* MCU is now physically running; track this for error path cleanup */
 	boot_csf_firmware(kbdev);
+	mcu_boot_attempted = true;

 	ret = parse_capabilities(kbdev);
 	if (ret != 0)
@@ -2751,7 +2756,9 @@ int kbase_csf_firmware_load_init(struct kbase_device *kbdev)
 	return 0;

 err_out:
-	kbase_csf_firmware_unload_term(kbdev);
+	if (mcu_boot_attempted)
+		kbase_hwcnt_backend_csf_on_after_mcu_off(&kbdev->hwcnt_gpu_iface);
+	kbase_csf_firmware_unload_term(kbdev);
 	return ret;
 }
